With this Git repository, the benchmark experiments and Figures 1, 7, 8, 9, and 10 can be reproduced.  
Please note that the analyses in the paper were performed using a high-throughput batch system.  
The system used consists of 11 nodes with 96 GB to 768 GB memory and 12 to 64 CPUs.  

This repository implements the same calculations on a local system, which may result in long computation times.  

To run the nhanes application and generate the plots, please follow these steps:
1) Open the R project "nhanes_application.Rproj".   
2) Open the script *01_prepare_data.R* in RStudio. You have to dowload the additional nhanes data about the prescription drugs as first, bevor you run this script. The details are listed in the header of *01_prepare_data.R*. This script preprocesses the NHANES pre-pandemic diabetes dataset, including data cleaning and feature preparation.
3) Once preprocessing is complete, run the script *02calculate_results.R*. This script trains all models used in the paperand stores all results required for the figure scripts. With the default settings provided in the script, the runtime is approximately 5 to 10 minutes on a standard local computer.
4) Open the script "03figure1.R" and/or "03figure7.R" and/or "03figure8.R" and/or "03figure9.R" and/or "03figure10.R" to generate the plots based on the data from step 3.  

If you want to use the original simulated data from the paper, please download the data from Zenodo (https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.19467860), unpack it, and store it in the "data" folder.  
In the scripts regarding building the figures, the corresponding lines for using this data are already included but commented out.  
Please uncomment these lines and comment out the lines that use the simulated data from the steps above.  

